Description: Fragment of oval handle from neck join to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine red-brown. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '259'. Name Andronikos. Probably from the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roan Museum, ABC 060.26.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (33)
